AKURE  – A chieftain of Peoples Dem­ocratic Party (PDP), Bode Obanla has commended Akoko traditional rulers’ deci­sion to support the re-election of the member of House of Representatives, representing Akoko North East/West Feder­al Constituency in Ondo State, Olubunmi Tunji-Ojo in 2023. Declaring his support for the re-election of the lawmak­er, Obanla, a community leader, revealed that the recent move by monarchs in the region to endorse Tunji-Ojo was unprec­edented, adding that it signified the popularity and general ac­ceptance of the lawmaker in the constituency. He emphasised that merit should always take priority over political affiliation as the monarchs did. APC Crisis Deepens As Buhari’s Imposition Of Adamu, Others Tear… Obasanjo Remains Quintessential Leader At 85, Says Sanwo-Olu The PDP chieftain noted that the chairman, House Com­mittee on Niger Delta Affairs has proved beyond reasonable doubts that he’s not just the man for the people but the man to move Akoko into its golden dispensation The Akoko Community leader, who is from Auga in Akoko North-East Local Gov­ernment Area of the state, com­mended the lawmaker for his unprecedented strides in the constituency. “When you see what BTO has done in ensuring the infra­structural and industrial devel­opment of his constituency, you will have no doubt that he is a leader who knows his onions and is well prepared for the job. “The poor conditions of medical centres in the region got changed for the better when Hon. Olubunmi Tunji-Ojo facil­itated the donations of mobile clinics, tricycles ambulance and other medical equipment for the constituency,” he said Speaking on the security situation in the constituency, Obanla applauded the impres­sive manner with which Tun­ji-Ojo solved the menace of insecurity in the constituency by convening a stakeholders meeting and donating patrol vehicles and logistics for the use of the Police and other se­curity agencies in the region.